flowRoot.flowPara: Initial state automatically attempts to determine the time zone.
Bubble inficates the time zone that has been set.
Next button becomes sensitive once a time zone has been set.
If the user accepts a manually set time zone, automatic time zone should be disabled.
Clearing the search entry reverts the time zone to the automatically determined one.

text.tspan: Search for nearby city to set the time zone.

flowRoot.flowPara: If automatic time zone fails, or isn't available, the user has to manually set one.

text.tspan: The time zone will be set automatically if your location can be found. You can also search for a city to set it yourself.

flowRoot.flowPara: Bubble inficates that the time zone that has been set.
Next button becomes sensitive once a time zone has been set.
If the user accepts a manually set time zone, automatic time zone should be disabled.
If there is no way to determine the location,alternative description string should be used: "Search for a city to set the time zone."
Using the search entry hides the process indicator.

text.tspan: The time zone will be set automatically if your location can be found. You can also search for a city to set it yourself.

flowRoot.flowPara: Selecting a search result replaces the automatically determined location with the manual one. Clearing the search entry reverts to the automatic location.
